com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.backend
Interface ITestCaseGenerator

public interface ITestCaseGenerator

Implementors of this interface represent KeYTestGen2 backend modules, i.e. they represent test case generators for a specific test framework, making use of the KeYTestGen2 runtime.

The API supports the following basic modes of operation:

    Generate a test suite only for a subset case methods in a class.
  • Generate a test suite for all methods in a class, with the option of including protected, private and methods inherited from java.lang.Object.

For any of the option above, the user has the option deciding the level of code coverage to be provided, by supplying an instance of ICodeCoverageParser. By default. Statement Coverage should be targeted.

Author:
christopher

                                       ICodeCoverageParser coverage,
                                       boolean includeProtected,
                                       boolean includePrivate,
                                       boolean includeNative)
                                       throws TestGeneratorException
Generates a set of JUnit test cases for a subset of methods in a Java source file.

Parameters:
source - path to the Java source file.
coverage - code coverage critera to be satisfied by the generated test cases. May be nulll, in which case a default statement coverage is used.
includeProtected - set to true to generate test cases also for protected methods.
includePrivate - set to true to generate test cases also for private methods.
includeNative - set to true to generate test cases also for methods inherited from java.lang.Object.
Returns:
a test suite for the framework targeted by the implementor.
Throws:
TestGeneratorException
